    <h3>Technical Details of Application</h3>

    <p style="font-size:18px">This is a demonstration application (no commercial use as is) using Python 3 with the
    Flask web application library, MongoDB, and Bootstrap with Jinja2 HTML template engine for Python, Flask and Jinja2
        being modelled on Django templates, and is hosted on CentOS 7 Linux on a Digital Ocean droplet, served with nginx and uWSGI.
    It uses the publicly available Croydon Highways Register 2015 version from a public website address, and a second
    Mongo 'collection' (originally a table in SQL-based MS Access). This second collection contains data on the Split
    Road, Split Borough and TfL side road status of the roads which have this in Croydon, but where a street does have
    a TfL side road, this data is currently mostly missing the TfL side road name (eg "A23").</p>
    <p style="font-size:18px">I have attempted to produce RESTful API type URLs (webpage addresses) for the street list and street report pages, by adding a separate
    consecutive numbered id field to the Mongo data, and passing this in the street report URL. Conversely, the street list URL contains the
    actual search terms entered by the user. In this way, unique street list or street report searches have their own
    unique, reasonably short and hopefully reasonably clear URL</p>

