    <h3>"Box C Streets" Meaning in this Application</h3>
    <p style="font-size:18px">In the Land Charges search process, the property buyer's solicitor may want to check status information for one or
    more side streets to the street where the property is addressed. For example, if the property is on or near a road
    junction, or if the back garden of a property abuts a busy street etc. then knowing whether or not this back road
    is a TfL maintained road or private road etc. could possibly affect a purchasing decision or property value.</p>

    <p style="font-size:18px">These side streets are called "Box C" streets on the standard CON29 form.</p>

    <p style="font-size:18px">In practice, perhaps much of this whole process has an 'insurance' value for the buyer; in most cases this data may not matter much
    to the average buyer or affect the property value much, but the total cost of a land charges search is usually low
    compared to the price of even a small property purchase.</p>

